    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/3–650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McDonald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-06T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 6, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>161. For personal attention of President and Secretary. Further re <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 158, March 6. For first time in many
                    months I ask your personal consideration. If projected Israel-Jordan five-year
                    nonaggression pact can be saved, US policy of peace and stability in <gloss
                        target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> will be immeasurably advanced. Abdullah sorely
                    needs and fully deserves our moral and economic support as he struggles against
                    intransigent forces which hope for Israel’s economic collapse demand indefinite
                    continuance anti-Israel boycott. Personal message of sympathy and support from
                    President to King might be decisive. Also friendly word of counsel in Cairo
                    urging sympathetic understanding Abdullah’s stand would diminish greatly forces
                    threatening King’s program conciliation. I think Dr. Bunche would agree that now
                    is opportune moment save Arab extremists from themselves.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McDonald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
